      "amount": "2 tbsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "salt",
      "amount": "to taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "black pepper",
      "amount": "to taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "garam masala",
      "amount": "1 tsp"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add chicken and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Remove chicken from the pan and set aside. Add onion and garlic to the pan; sauté for an additional minute.",
    "Add green and red bell peppers to the pan, stir-fry for 2-3 minutes or until they start to soften.",
    "Return chicken to the pan with vegetables. Add ginger, soy sauce, vinegar, garam masala, salt, and pepper. Stir well to combine.",
    "Cook until most of the liquid is evaporated and the chicken is fully cooked through, about 5 more minutes.",
    "Serve hot as a main dish or side."
